1268 [[nodiscard]] constexpr bool operator==(const bitset& other) const noexcept
1269 {
1270 for (size_type i = 0; i < m_full_storage_size; ++i)
1271 {
1272 if (m_data[i] != other.m_data[i])
1273 return false;
1274 }
1275 if (m_partial_size)
1276 {
1277 const BlockType mask = (1 << m_partial_size) - 1;
1278 if ((m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask) != (other.m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask))
1279 return false;
1280 }
1281 return true;
1282 }

1408 [[nodiscard]] constexpr bitset operator>>(const size_type& shift) const noexcept
1409 {
1410 bitset result;
1411
1412 // Number of blocks to shift
1413 const size_type block_shift = shift / m_block_size;
1414
1415 // Number of bits to shift within a block
1416 const size_type bit_shift = shift % m_block_size;
1417
1418 // Shift across multiple blocks
1419 for (size_type i = 0; i < m_storage_size; ++i)
1420 {
1421 // Handle shifting within a block
1422 result.m_data[i] = (i + block_shift < m_storage_size) ?
1423 (m_data[i + block_shift] >> bit_shift) :
1424 0; // If shifting exceeds block boundaries, fill with zeros
1425 // If there are remaining bits to shift to the next block
1426 if (bit_shift > 0 && i + block_shift + 1 < m_storage_size)
1427 {
1428 // Shift the remaining bits to the next block
1429 result.m_data[i] |= (m_data[i + block_shift + 1] << (m_block_size - bit_shift));
1430 }
1431 }
1432
1433 return result;
1434 }

1619 {
1620 return;

2187 for (uint16_t i = 0; i < end % m_block_size; ++i)
2188 m_data[end / m_block_size] &= ~(BlockType{1} << i);
2189 }
2190 else
2191 to_sub = 0;
2192
2193 if (std::is_constant_evaluated())
2194 {
2195 for (size_type i = begin / m_block_size + to_add; i < end / m_block_size; ++i)
2196 m_data[i] = 0;
2197 }
2198 else
2199 ::memset(m_data + begin / m_block_size + to_add, 0, (end - begin) / m_block_size * sizeof(BlockType) - to_sub);
2200 }

2247 constexpr void fill_range_optimized(const size_type& begin, const size_type& end, const size_type& step, const bool value) noexcept
2248 {
2249 // Initialize variables
2250 size_type blocks_size, current_block = begin / m_block_size + 1 + step / m_block_size, current_offset = 0;
2251
2252 const size_type end_block = end / m_block_size + (end % m_block_size ? 1 : 0);
2253
2254 // Determine the size of blocks based on step and block size
2255 if ((step % 2 || step <= m_block_size) && m_block_size % step) {
2256 blocks_size = (std::min)(m_storage_size, step);
2257 }
2258 else if (!(m_block_size % step))
2259 blocks_size = 1;
2260 else if (!(step % m_block_size))
2261 blocks_size = step / m_block_size;
2262 else
2263 {
2264 // GCD of step and m_block_size
2265 if (step % m_block_size)
2266 {
2267 size_type a = step, b = m_block_size, t = m_block_size;
2268 while (b) {
2269 t = b;
2270 b = a % b;
2271 a = t;
2272 }
2273 blocks_size = a;
2274 }
2275 else
2276 blocks_size = 1;
2277 }
2278
2279
2280
2281 // Calculate the offset
2282 uint16_t offset = (step - (m_block_size - begin % m_block_size) % step) % step;
2283
2284 // Create and apply the beginning block
2285 {
2286 const uint16_t end_bit = (begin / m_block_size == end / m_block_size) ? end % m_block_size : m_block_size;
2287 if (value)
2288 {
2289 for (uint16_t i = begin % m_block_size; i < end_bit; i += step)
2290 m_data[begin / m_block_size] |= BlockType{ 1 } << i;
2291 }
2292 else
2293 {
2294 for (uint16_t i = begin % m_block_size; i < end_bit; i += step)
2295 m_data[begin / m_block_size] &= ~(BlockType{ 1 } << i);
2296 }
2297 }
2298
2299
2300 // Fill with appropriate block
2301 std::cout << blocks_size << " blocks\n";
2302 std::cout << (std::min)(blocks_size, m_storage_size) << " blocks\n";
2303 for (size_type i = 0; i < (std::min)(blocks_size, m_storage_size); ++i)
2304 {
2305 std::cout << "offset: " << offset << '\n';
2306
2307 // Generate block for the current iteration
2308 BlockType block = 0;
2309
2310 if (value)
2311 {
2312 for (uint16_t j = !i ? offset : 0; j < m_block_size; ++j)
2313 {
2314 //std::cout << current_block * m_block_size + j - offset << '\n';
2315 if (!((i * m_block_size + j - offset) % step))
2316 block |= BlockType{ 1 } << j;
2317 }
2318 }
2319 else
2320 {
2321 block = (std::numeric_limits<BlockType>::max)();
2322 for (uint16_t j = !i ? offset : 0; j < m_block_size; ++j)
2323 {
2324 if (!((i * m_block_size + j - offset) % step))
2325 block &= ~(BlockType{ 1 } << j);
2326 }
2327 }
2328
2329 // print the block
2330 for (uint16_t j = 0; j < m_block_size; ++j)
2331 {
2332 std::cout << ((block & BlockType{ 1 } << j) >> j);
2333 }
2334
2335 std::cout << '\n';
2336
2337 // Apply the block
2338 for (size_type j = current_block++; j < m_storage_size; j += blocks_size)
2339 {
2340 if (value)
2341 *(m_data + j) |= block;
2342 else
2343 *(m_data + j) &= block;
2344 }
2345 offset = (step - (m_block_size - offset % m_block_size) % step) % step;
2346 }
2347 }

2517 {
2518 size_type to_add = 1;

2520 {
2521 for (uint16_t i = begin % m_block_size; i < m_block_size; ++i)
2522 m_data[begin / m_block_size] ^= BlockType{1} << i;

4181 [[nodiscard]] Elem* to_c_string(const Elem& set_chr = '1', const Elem& rst_chr = '0') const noexcept
4182 {

4192 *(result + (m_storage_size - 1) * m_block_size + i) = m_data[i] & BlockType{ 1 } << i ? set_chr : rst_chr;

4205 template <unsigned_integer T>
4206 void _from_integer(const T& value) noexcept
4207 {
4208 if (sizeof(T) <= sizeof(BlockType))
4209 {
4210 if (m_storage_size != 1)
4211 {
4212 delete[] m_data;
4213 m_data = new BlockType;
4214 m_storage_size = 1;
4215 m_size = sizeof(T) * 8;
4216 }
4217 *m_data = ~static_cast<BlockType>((std::numeric_limits<T>::max)()) | value;
4218 return;
4219 }
4220
4221 constexpr uint16_t diff = sizeof(T) / sizeof(BlockType);
4222
4223 if (m_storage_size != diff)
4224 {
4225 delete[] m_data;
4226 m_data = new BlockType[diff];
4227 m_storage_size = diff;
4228 m_size = sizeof(T) * 8;
4229 }
4230
4231 for (uint16_t i = 0; i < diff; ++i)
4232 {
4233 m_data[i] = value >> i * m_block_size;
4234 }
4235 }

4244 template <unsigned_integer T>
4245 [[nodiscard]] T to_integer() const noexcept
4246 {
4247 if constexpr (sizeof(T) <= sizeof(BlockType))
4248 return m_data[0];
4249
4250 constexpr uint16_t diff = sizeof(T) / sizeof(BlockType);
4251 T result = 0;
4252 for (int16_t i = 0; i < diff; ++i)
4253 result |= static_cast<T>(m_data[i]) << i * m_block_size;
4254
4255 return result;

4267 [[nodiscard]] bool operator==(const dynamic_bitset& other) const noexcept
4268 {
4269 if (m_size != other.m_size)
4270 return false;
4271 for (size_type i = 0; i < m_storage_size - !!m_partial_size; ++i)
4272 {
4273 if (m_data[i] != other.m_data[i])
4274 return false;
4275 }
4276 if (m_partial_size)
4277 {
4278 const BlockType mask = (1 << m_partial_size) - 1;
4279 if ((m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask) != (other.m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask))
4280 return false;
4281 }
4282 return true;
4283 }
4284
4290 [[nodiscard]] bool operator!=(const dynamic_bitset& other) const noexcept
4291 {
4292 if (m_size != other.m_size)
4293 for (size_type i = 0; i < m_storage_size - !!m_partial_size; ++i)
4294 {
4295 if (m_data[i] == other.m_data[i])
4296 return false;
4297 }
4298 if (m_partial_size)
4299 {
4300 const BlockType mask = (1 << m_partial_size) - 1;
4301 if ((m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask) == (other.m_data[m_storage_size - 1] & mask))
4302 return false;
4303 }
4304 return true;
4305 }

4398 [[nodiscard]] constexpr dynamic_bitset operator>>(const size_type& shift) const noexcept
4399 {
4400 dynamic_bitset result(m_size);
4401
4402 // Number of blocks to shift
4403 const size_type block_shift = shift / m_block_size;
4404
4405 // Number of bits to shift within a block
4406 const size_type bit_shift = shift % m_block_size;
4407
4408 // Shift across multiple blocks
4409 for (size_type i = 0; i < m_storage_size; ++i)
4410 {
4411 // Handle shifting within a block
4412 result.m_data[i] = (i + block_shift < m_storage_size) ?
4413 (m_data[i + block_shift] >> bit_shift) :
4414 0; // If shifting exceeds block boundaries, fill with zeros
4415 // If there are remaining bits to shift to the next block
4416 if (bit_shift > 0 && i + block_shift + 1 < m_storage_size)
4417 {
4418 // Shift the remaining bits to the next block
4419 result.m_data[i] |= (m_data[i + block_shift + 1] << (m_block_size - bit_shift));
4420 }
4421 }
4422
4423 return result;
4424 }

4957 blocks_size = (std::min)(m_storage_size, step);

5456 void resize(const size_type& new_size)
5457 {

5459 return;
5460
5461 if (!new_size)
5462 {
5463 m_partial_size = m_storage_size = m_size = 0;
5464 if (m_data)
5465 {
5466 delete[] m_data;
5467 }
5468 m_data = nullptr;
5469 return;
5470 }

5472 BlockType* new_data = new BlockType[new_size];
5473 if (m_data)
5474 {
5475 if (m_storage_size < new_size)
5476 {
5477 std::copy(m_data, m_data + m_storage_size, new_data);
5478 ::memset(new_data + m_storage_size, 0, (new_size - m_storage_size) * sizeof(BlockType)); // ensure 0 initialization
5479 }
5480 else
5481 {
5482 std::copy(m_data, m_data + new_size, new_data);
5483 }
5484 delete[] m_data;
5485 }
5486 m_partial_size = new_size % m_block_size;
5487 m_storage_size = new_size / m_block_size + !!m_partial_size;
5488 m_size = new_size;
5489 m_data = new_data;

5496 void push_back(const bool value)
5497 {
5498 if (!(m_size++ % m_block_size))
5499 {
5500 m_partial_size = 0;
5501 BlockType* new_data = new BlockType[++m_storage_size];
5502 if (m_data)

5504 std::copy(m_data, m_data + m_storage_size, new_data);

5506 }
5507 *(new_data + m_storage_size - 1) = 0;
5508 m_data = new_data;
5509 }
5510 else

5513 }

5515 m_data[m_storage_size - 1] |= BlockType{ 1 } << m_partial_size - 1;
5516 else
5517 m_data[m_storage_size - 1] &= ~(BlockType{ 1 } << m_partial_size - 1);
5518 }

5555 void insert(const size_type& index, const bool value)
5556 {
5557 if (index == m_size)
5558 {
5559 push_back(value);
5560 return;
5561 }
5562
5563 if (!(m_size % m_block_size))
5564 {
5565 m_partial_size = 0;
5566 BlockType* new_data = new BlockType[++m_storage_size];
5567 if (m_data)
5568 {
5569 // copy everything prepending the bit
5570 for (size_type i = 0; i < index; ++i)
5571 {
5572 if (test(i))
5573 *(new_data + i / m_block_size) |= BlockType{ 1 } << i % m_block_size;
5574 else
5575 *(new_data + i / m_block_size) &= ~(BlockType{ 1 } << i % m_block_size);
5576 }
5577 // copy everything appending the bit
5578 for (size_type i = index; i < m_size; ++i)
5579 {
5580 if (test(i))
5581 *(new_data + (i + 1) / m_block_size) |= BlockType{ 1 } << (i + 1) % m_block_size;
5582 else
5583 *(new_data + (i + 1) / m_block_size) &= ~(BlockType{ 1 } << (i + 1) % m_block_size);
5584 }
5585 delete[] m_data;
5586 m_data = new_data;
5587 set(index, value);
5588 }
5589 m_data = new_data;
5590 }
5591 else
5592 {
5593 const dynamic_bitset tmp_copy(*this);
5594 // copy everything appending the bit
5595 for (size_type i = index; i < m_size; ++i)
5596 {
5597 set(i + 1, tmp_copy.test(i));
5598 }
5599 set(index, value);
5600 ++m_partial_size;
5601 }
5602 ++m_size;
5603 }

5652 void insert_block(const size_type& index, const BlockType& block)
5653 {
5654 if (index == m_storage_size)
5655 {
5656 push_back_block(block);
5657 return;
5658 }
5659
5660 BlockType* new_data = new BlockType[m_storage_size + 1];
5661 if (m_data)
5662 {
5663 // copy everything prepending the block
5664 for (size_type i = 0; i < index; ++i)
5665 *(new_data + i) = *(m_data + i);
5666
5667 // copy everything appending the block
5668 for (size_type i = index; i < m_storage_size; ++i)
5669 *(new_data + i + 1) = *(m_data + i);
5670 delete[] m_data;
5671 }
5672
5673 m_size += m_block_size;
5674 ++m_storage_size;
5675 m_data = new_data;
5676
5677 *(new_data + index) = block;
5678 }
